HEADWORD: Ambit
<hw>Am"bit</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ambitus</ets> circuit, fr. <ets>ambire</ets> to go around. See
<er>Ambient</er>.]</ety> <def>Circuit or compass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His great parts did not live within a small <qex>ambit</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
